commitResults.messageTitle: Added functionality for Level-2. Added some comments to the code.

Added functionality for Level-7. - Created a DukeSaveLoad class to handle the saving and loading of data - Created "toSaveFileString" methods for Task class to help with saving and loading of data - Edited Duke to save data whenever its internal list changes

Added functionality for Level-8 - Created DukeDateTime class to handle all date and time computation - Edited Duke's input parsing to work with specific formats for date and time - Edited EventTask and DeadlineTask to use DukeDateTime to encode timings - Fixed a bug where TaskList would use the user input index rather than the actual index to complete tasks

Refactored code to be cleaner + better fitting to OOP standards. - Decision-making moved out of Duke into UserInputProcessor - Created TextToTaskTranslator to parse Text inputs into Tasks (Text -> Task translation no longer part of Decision-Making) - Duke's text lines moved out of Duke into DukeUi - Deleted all custom Exceptions other than DukeException - All DukeExceptions, rather than having a hard-coded error message, will call upon the appropriate error message in DukeUi during instantiation. - Changed DukeSaveLoad (and all saving and loading operations to use "Serializable" rather than String-parsing) - Changed Task from an Interface to an Abstract Class, changed each Task accordingly - Changed implementation of DukeDateTime and created - Created DukeDuration class - EventTask uses DukeDuration to keep track of its timing - Added "Nuke" functionality to Duke to allow it to destroy all Tasks in the list
